{pc}$, consistent\nwith three-dimensional dust maps. Action calculations and orbit integrations,\nwhich assume the global and local midplanes are identical, are likely to\ninclude this induced error, depending on the volume considered. Variation in\nthe local standard of rest or distance to the Galactic center causes similar\nissues. The variation of the midplane must be taken into account when\nperforming dynamical analysis across the large regions of the disk accessible\nto Gaia and future missions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 May 2019 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Aug 2019 20:44:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-11"}
