 trajectory corresponding to a sudden quench to the\ncritical point, the density of states is shown to grow in a manner where the\ntime after the quench plays the role of the inverse detuning from the critical\npoint.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 May 2019 00:10:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Aug 2019 11:38:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-04"}
